5:
Still hitting the books, huh? How does
a tea break sound?
10:
That sounds great, actually.
How about you, Rain?
15: Rain... you still with us, buddy?
19:
Your final exam is coming up soon,
isn't it, Rain?
23: Yeah... It's sink or swim now.
28:
I mean, you can already handle a ship
on your own as a sailor, right? You don't
need a test score to tell you that.
32:
It is not only seafaring. 
If Rain graduates, he will become a 
sublieutenant—a position of 
leadership.
36:
Is that what's got you so worried about
your test?
40:
Still not cut out for classroom learning,
huh?
45:
No, not exactly. Stella's helped me
get over that.
49:
I'm quite embarrassed to admit this,
but...
53:
So part of the test involves
a long-distance swim?
57:
I never thought you of all people
would be averse to swimming.
61:
I'm usually able to walk on water,
so I've never really needed to get better
at it...
65: The solution is simple, is it not? Practice.
70:
Yes, I suppose. I... I just don't want to
embarrass myself in front of everyone.
75: You didn't have to throw me in!
78:
Less talkin', more swimmin'. You don't
wanna keep your fan club waiting,
right?
83:
The next portion of your exam will be
long-distance swimming. Cadet Rain,
are you ready?
94:
Spectators, please refrain from any
outbursts so that we may proceed.
Now then, if you'd please.
97:
Hey...
You guys see something out there?
102: Hmm. We may need to reschedule this.
105:
Get back here, Rain!
There's a monster out there!
110:
I can't! There's a ship!
And it's a civilian vessel!
122:
Hey! Get in contact!
Request cannon fire, on the double!
131:
There should be cannons near the
waterfront. Let's move!
137: I... I managed to swim the entire way!
142:
Sublieutenant Rain, Gaea Naval
Academy graduate, reporting for duty!
149:
Second Lieutenant, huh?
Has a nice ring to it.
153:
I'll whip up something to celebrate!
You say something too, Nimbus.
157:
Why'd you go off on your own back
there?
163:
About that... I apologize. The officers
at the academy gave me an earful
about it too.
168:
They're right. If I'm to be in charge of
people, I'll need to learn to trust in them.
174:
I wouldn't have made it this far without
everyone's help. Thank you.
176:
That being said... would it be all right if
I stuck around for a little longer?
